-- Czech Stocks: Erste, New World Resources Move in Prague Trading
-- B y   K r y s t o f   C h a m o n i k o l a s
-- 2011-12-19T17:00:29Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-12-19/czech-stocks-erste-new-world-resources-move-in-prague-trading.html
The  Czech Republic ’s  PX (PX)  equity index
dropped 0.5 percent to 852.8 at the close in Prague, adding to a
1.9 percent decline last week.  The following were among the most active stocks on the
Prague Stock Exchange today. Stock symbols follow company names.  Erste Group Bank AG (RBAG)   tumbled 4.7 percent to 303.8
koruna, snapping a two-day rally. The Austrian company today
issued 4 million new shares to pay for a stake in Romania’s
Banca Comerciala Romana SA.  New World Resources Plc (NWR)  , the biggest coking-coal
producer in the Czech Republic, fell 0.8 percent to 123 koruna,
its lowest close 2 1/2 months.  Europe ’s benchmark coal  futures 
contracts slipped for a sixth day to $112.9 a metric ton in the
Netherlands.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Krystof Chamonikolas in  Prague  at 
